&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[About the role]&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Head of Technology, Platform Business&lt;/strong&gt; to lead the &lt;strong&gt;architecture, execution, and scale&lt;/strong&gt; of this ecosystem. This role requires a strong emphasis on UPI-native systems, high-scale consumer payments, and regulated platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[Key Responsibilities]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;UPI &amp;amp; payments infrastructure: TPAP lifecycle from application through NPCI compliance to production, PSP/TSP integrations, VPA management, mandate and autopay flows, settlement &amp;amp; reconciliation, and payment failure handling. Designing for 3B+ annual transactions at scale. You’ll own the full payments stack: from how a transaction is initiated to how it settles and reconciles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Platform services: microservices architecture covering auth, order orchestration, wallet/ledger, issuance, discovery, cohorts, and notifications. Defining API contracts, enforcing event-driven patterns, building saga-based distributed transaction orchestration, and ensuring idempotency across every service boundary.&lt;/li&gt;
